10 SECTION 4. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
11 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 4604 of Title 68, unless there
12 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
13 A. An eligible venue entity may receive a rebate of either
14 sales tax or mixed beverage gross receipts tax or both such taxes
15 based upon such revenues collected by or remitted by the entity at
16 which the eligible performance occurs as further provided by this
17 section.
18 B. A rebate of sales tax revenue shall be applicable to state
19 sales tax collected by the eligible venue entity from sales of
20 tangible personal property occurring during the period of time
21 beginning twelve (12) hours prior to the scheduled start time for a
22 musical performance at the eligible venue and ending twelve (12)
23 hours after the scheduled start time for a musical performance at
24 the eligible venue.
